1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,800
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:06,800
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:12,400
My name is Kathryn and today we have an elementary level lesson for you all about computers.
我是Kathryn，今天我们为大家带来一节关于电脑的基础课程。

4
00:00:12,400 --> 00:00:13,400
That's right.
没错。

5
00:00:13,400 --> 00:00:19,600
So we are going to take a look at some of the basic parts of a computer and also about
所以我们要看看电脑的一些基本部件，还有关于

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:24,040
bad programs that could affect your computer and make it not work.
可能影响电脑并导致它无法正常工作的坏程序。

7
00:00:24,040 --> 00:00:25,040
That's right.
没错。

8
00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:33,120
So to get going, we have a verb for you that we're going to look at in vocabulary preview.
那么开始之前，我们有一个动词，会在词汇预览中介绍。

9
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,120
Vocabulary preview.
词汇预览。

10
00:00:34,120 --> 00:00:35,120
All right.
好的。

11
00:00:35,120 --> 00:00:41,400
So today on vocabulary preview, we have a verb as you said, and it's to crash.
今天在词汇预览中，我们有一个动词，就像你说的，是“crash”。

12
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,400
To crash.
“Crash”。

13
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:43,400
Okay.
好的。

14
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:48,760
This has a couple of different meanings, but in today's dialogue, this means for your computer
这个词有几个不同的意思，但在今天的对话中，它指的是你的电脑

15
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:52,240
to shut down or to freeze or to stop working.
关机、死机或停止工作。

16
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,240
Right.
对。

17
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:55,520
So maybe you heard of a car crash, right?
你可能听说过“car crash”（车祸），对吧？

18
00:00:55,520 --> 00:00:57,720
When two cars, bam, hit each other.
就是两辆车“砰”地撞在一起。

19
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:01,160
In this case, your computer is just not working anymore.
在这里，你的电脑就是不再工作了。

20
00:01:01,160 --> 00:01:02,440
It stopped working.
它停止工作了。

21
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:03,440
It freezes.
它死机了。

22
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:04,440
That's right.
没错。

23
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,720
So you can't use it.
所以你就没法用了。

24
00:01:05,720 --> 00:01:10,400
So my computer crashed is a way to say my computer stopped working.
所以“my computer crashed”就是说我的电脑停止工作了。

25
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:11,520
Okay.
好的。

26
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:14,280
So that's a word that we're going to listen in our dialogue today.
这就是我们今天对话中会听到的一个词。

27
00:01:14,280 --> 00:01:23,120
Why don't we jump right into it and we'll be back shortly.
我们直接进入对话吧，稍后再回来。

28
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:24,120
Hello.
你好。

29
00:01:24,120 --> 00:01:25,720
Thanks for calling one, two, three tech help.
感谢拨打123技术支持热线。

30
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:26,720
I'm Todd.
我是Todd。

31
00:01:26,720 --> 00:01:27,720
How can I help you?
有什么可以帮您的？

32
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:28,720
Hello.
你好。

33
00:01:28,720 --> 00:01:30,720
Can you help me on my computer?
你能帮我看看我的电脑吗？

34
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,120
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

35
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:33,120
It's okay, sir.
没事的，先生。

36
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,120
Calm down.
冷静点。

37
00:01:34,120 --> 00:01:35,120
What happened?
发生什么事了？

38
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:36,760
I turned on my laptop and it broke.
我打开笔记本电脑，它就坏了。

39
00:01:36,760 --> 00:01:39,000
I mean, the monitor went black.
我是说，显示器变黑了。

40
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,160
Okay, sir.
好的，先生。

41
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:42,720
It sounds like you might have a virus.
听起来你可能中了病毒。

42
00:01:42,720 --> 00:01:43,920
I don't feel sick.
我没觉得不舒服啊。

43
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:45,480
Let me check.
让我检查一下。

44
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,480
Nope.
没有。

45
00:01:46,480 --> 00:01:47,480
No fever.
没发烧。

46
00:01:47,480 --> 00:01:48,480
I'm fine.
我很好。

47
00:01:48,480 --> 00:01:51,000
No, your computer might have a virus.
不，是你的电脑可能中了病毒。

48
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,160
I mean, it has a bad program on it.
我是说，它上面有个坏程序。

49
00:01:54,160 --> 00:01:55,840
Maybe that's why it crashed.
也许这就是它崩溃的原因。

50
00:01:55,840 --> 00:02:01,160
I recommend that you run an antivirus program in order to safely remove any unwanted spyware
我建议你运行一个杀毒程序，以便安全地移除任何不需要的间谍软件

51
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:02,160
or trojans.
或木马。

52
00:02:02,160 --> 00:02:03,160
Phew.
呼。

53
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,160
Wait a minute.
等一下。

54
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,160
Crash, spyware, trojans.
崩溃、间谍软件、木马。

55
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:06,160
What?
什么？

56
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:07,160
Where?
在哪？

57
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:08,160
When?
什么时候？

58
00:02:08,160 --> 00:02:09,160
All right.
好的。

59
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:18,760
So lots of great technology words today.
今天有很多很棒的技术词汇。

60
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:24,640
Let's take a look at a few of them in Language Takeaway.
我们来看看“语言要点”中的几个。

61
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:25,640
Language Takeaway.
语言要点。

62
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,080
All right.
好的。

63
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:30,240
So let's start off with our first word.
我们先从第一个词开始。

64
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:34,040
You've probably heard it before, but let's go over it just in case.
你可能以前听过，但为了以防万一，我们还是过一遍。

65
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,040
A laptop.
“Laptop”（笔记本电脑）。

66
00:02:35,040 --> 00:02:36,040
Laptop.
“Laptop”。

67
00:02:36,040 --> 00:02:39,460
A laptop is a kind of computer.
笔记本电脑是一种电脑。

68
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,040
We have desktop, laptop.
我们有台式机和笔记本电脑。

69
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:42,040
Right.
对。

70
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:44,560
So your lap is the top part of your legs.
你的“lap”就是大腿的上部。

71
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:50,720
So a laptop computer is a small portable computer that you can take with you anywhere.
所以笔记本电脑是一种小巧便携的电脑，你可以随身携带。

72
00:02:50,720 --> 00:02:51,720
That's right.
没错。

73
00:02:51,720 --> 00:02:55,000
A lot of students have laptops and businessmen as well.
很多学生和商务人士都有笔记本电脑。

74
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,360
So you mentioned the opposite would be a desktop.
你提到了它的反义词是“desktop”（台式机）。

75
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,360
Right.
对。

76
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:00,280
So it sits on top of a desk.
所以它放在桌子上。

77
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,280
Okay.
好的。

78
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:07,080
So both a desktop and a laptop have monitors, a computer monitor.
台式机和笔记本电脑都有显示器，也就是电脑显示器。

79
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:10,720
So a monitor is like a TV for your computer.
显示器就像电脑的电视。

80
00:03:10,720 --> 00:03:13,160
It's where you can see what you're doing.
你可以在上面看到你在做什么。

81
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:14,160
Okay.
好的。

82
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:17,640
So let's call it a monitor or a screen maybe.
那我们叫它显示器或者屏幕吧。

83
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:25,440
You can also use the word screen, but monitor is the technical word for the, usually a box,
你也可以用“屏幕”这个词，但“显示器”是技术术语，通常指一个盒子，

84
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:28,080
like a TV that goes with the desktop computer.
就像和台式电脑配套的电视一样。

85
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,080
Okay.
好的。

86
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,080
Very good.
很好。

87
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:35,560
So Todd, the computer guy said, Hey, I think your computer might have a virus.
所以，电脑专家托德说：“嘿，我觉得你的电脑可能中病毒了。”

88
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:37,560
Ooh, that doesn't sound good.
哦，听起来不妙。

89
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,560
Yeah.
是啊。

90
00:03:38,560 --> 00:03:39,560
A virus.
病毒。

91
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:42,360
So I guess you know what a virus is when you get sick, right?
我想你知道生病时“病毒”是什么意思，对吧？

92
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:44,120
You get the flu or the cold.
你会得流感或感冒。

93
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,120
That's right.
没错。

94
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:49,840
You can say I have a virus, but how can a computer have a virus?
你可以说“我感染了病毒”，但电脑怎么会中病毒呢？

95
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:54,440
This means it's a program that is designed to hurt your computer.
这意味着它是一个旨在伤害你电脑的程序。

96
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,440
All right.
好的。

97
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,720
So it's like your computer is sick and it doesn't work.
所以就像你的电脑生病了，无法正常工作。

98
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:01,400
So a virus might make your computer crash.
所以病毒可能导致你的电脑崩溃。

99
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:02,400
Exactly.
没错。

100
00:04:02,400 --> 00:04:07,240
So in order to avoid this, what we need is an antivirus program.
所以为了避免这种情况，我们需要一个杀毒程序。

101
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,240
Okay.
好的。

102
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:10,920
So virus is a bad thing.
所以病毒是坏东西。

103
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:11,920
Antivirus is a good thing.
杀毒是好事。

104
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:18,160
An antivirus program is a program that protects your computer from viruses.
杀毒程序是一个保护你电脑免受病毒侵害的程序。

105
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:20,320
So you would say antivirus.
所以你会说“杀毒”。

106
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:27,160
You might've heard of a very famous program called Norton antivirus or McAfee antivirus.
你可能听说过一个很有名的程序叫诺顿杀毒或迈克菲杀毒。

107
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,160
These are brands.
这些都是品牌。

108
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,160
Okay.
好的。

109
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:30,560
Very good.
很好。

110
00:04:30,560 --> 00:04:35,000
So those are some of the main technical terms that we have on Language Takeaway.
这些就是我们在“语言要点”部分学到的一些主要技术术语。

111
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:37,920
Why don't we listen to our dialogue quickly once again.
我们快速再听一遍对话吧。

112
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:43,320
Why don't we listen to our dialogue quickly again and we'll be back with Fluency Builder.
我们快速再听一遍对话，然后回来进行“流利度训练”。

113
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:44,840
Hello.
你好。

114
