Thanks for calling 123 Tech Help.
感谢致电123技术帮助。

115
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,160
I'm Todd.
我是托德。

116
00:04:50,160 --> 00:04:51,160
How can I help you?
有什么可以帮您？

117
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,160
Hello.
你好。

118
00:04:52,160 --> 00:04:53,160
Can you help me?
你能帮我吗？

119
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,160
My computer.
我的电脑。

120
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:55,840
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

121
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,000
It's okay, sir.
没事的，先生。

122
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,000
Calm down.
冷静点。

123
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,000
What happened?
发生什么事了？

124
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,680
I turned on my laptop and it broke.
我打开笔记本电脑，它就坏了。

125
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,800
I mean, the monitor went black.
我是说，显示器变黑了。

126
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:03,880
Okay, sir.
好的，先生。

127
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:06,600
It sounds like you might have a virus.
听起来你可能中病毒了。

128
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,000
I don't feel sick.
我没觉得不舒服啊。

129
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:09,640
Let me check.
让我检查一下。

130
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:10,640
Nope.
没有。

131
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,640
No fever.
没发烧。

132
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:12,640
I'm fine.
我很好。

133
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:15,040
No, your computer might have a virus.
不，是你的电脑可能中病毒了。

134
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:18,080
I mean, it has a bad program on it.
我是说，它里面有个坏程序。

135
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:19,840
Maybe that's why it crashed.
也许这就是它崩溃的原因。

136
00:05:19,840 --> 00:05:25,120
I recommend that you run an antivirus program in order to safely remove any unwanted spyware
我建议你运行一个杀毒程序，以便安全地移除任何不需要的间谍软件

137
00:05:25,120 --> 00:05:26,960
or Trojans.
或木马。

138
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,400
Phew.
呼。

139
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,720
Wait a minute.
等一下。

140
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,720
Crash.
崩溃。

141
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:31,720
Spyware.
间谍软件。

142
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:32,720
Trojans.
木马。

143
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,720
What?
什么？

144
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,720
Where?
哪里？

145
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:35,720
When?
什么时候？

146
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,720
I don't know.
我不知道。

147
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,720
I'm just kidding.
我只是开玩笑。

148
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,720
All right.
好的。

149
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,720
We're back.
我们回来了。

150
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:45,160
So now, let's start off with three key phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在，我们从“流利度训练”的三个关键短语开始。

151
00:05:45,160 --> 00:05:47,880
This first phrase is one that I know you use a lot.
第一个短语我知道你经常用。

152
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:48,880
I use it too.
我也用。

153
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:50,560
We say, oh man.
我们说“哦，天哪”。

154
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,040
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

155
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:57,360
So now, depending on the tone, it can mean different things, right?
所以，根据语气不同，它可以表示不同的意思，对吧？

156
00:05:57,360 --> 00:05:59,320
So in this case, what does it mean?
那么在这个例子中，它是什么意思？

157
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:03,760
So the man who's having problems with his computer says, my computer.
那个电脑出问题的男人说：“我的电脑。”

158
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:05,320
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

159
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:06,320
Right.
对。

160
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:07,320
He seems a little bit anguished.
他看起来有点痛苦。

161
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:08,320
Disappointed.
失望。

162
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:09,320
Yeah.
是的。

163
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,320
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

164
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,320
So, it's an interjection.
所以，这是一个感叹词。

165
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,320
That's right.
没错。

166
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:16,000
So you can say, oh man, my computer crashed.
所以你可以说，哦，天哪，我的电脑死机了。

167
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Right.
对。

168
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:19,160
Oh man, you're always late.
哦，天哪，你总是迟到。

169
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:21,520
Now you can also say it for maybe surprise.
你也可以用它来表示惊讶。

170
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,240
Like oh man.
比如，哦，天哪。

171
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:27,800
So when you're excited about something, oh man, this computer game is awesome.
所以当你对某事感到兴奋时，哦，天哪，这个电脑游戏太棒了。

172
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,800
Mm-hmm.
嗯哼。

173
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:29,800
Okay.
好的。

174
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:35,080
So it's just a way of expressing maybe disappointment or in some cases, excitement.
所以它只是一种表达失望或某些情况下兴奋的方式。

175
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,080
Right.
对。

176
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,800
So think about the way that you say it.
所以想想你说话的方式。

177
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,800
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

178
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,800
Oh man.
哦，天哪。

179
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,800
Okay.
好的。

180
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:45,720
So now, the guy, Todd, he tells him, hey sir, it's okay.
所以现在，那个家伙，托德，他对他说，嘿，先生，没事的。

181
00:06:45,720 --> 00:06:46,720
Calm down.
冷静点。

182
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:47,720
Right?
对吧？

183
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:48,720
Okay.
好的。

184
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:51,560
So this might be funny sounding because we say calm.
所以这听起来可能有点好笑，因为我们说“冷静”。

185
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,800
So be calm.
所以要冷静。

186
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,800
Calm down.
冷静下来。

187
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:54,920
This is a phrase.
